			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the best solution would be to add more pet focii that stack with the current focii but are more specialized in their use. I think the dependance on 1 drop is definitely not good for progression. Why can't we have several classes of pet foci to increase max hit, atk, ac, hps, crits, etc...? They already did foci for spells, why not foci for pets. This will scale all pets (though of course, I'd prefer some really great mage ones).
<br />

<br />
Also, another issue is how good can pet tanking get before it's too good? I definitely agree that pet mitigation needs improvement and we aren't even close to game breaking with a decent upgrade around say 15% (even baseline). Further upgrades can be done through pet AC foci. However, consider how good pet groups will become should mitigation approach even that of a pre-Elly warrior. Mitigation needs improvement so pet can adequately offtank but not so much where pet groups are clearly superior in most cases. In some areas, it needs to be clearly seen that no matter the number of pets, it would have been preferable to have a single warrior tanking rather than expend the mana to chain more pets. 
<br />

<br />
Rather than concentrate too much on mitigation, I can live with a decent improvement there and just concentrate the rest of pet upgrades on the dps department. In short, make them summoned rangers <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> I think this will also satisfy those concerned with balancing against DC pets. Our pets will put out similar dps but drop quicker than DC pets. However, DC pets can't hold aggro so their hps/mitigation goes to waste most of the time anyways. Most people, when talking about DC pets, are really talking about their dps. I'm fine with a paper tank if it makes up for it in damage.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Zyphanus on Mon Feb 02, 2004 5:22 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
