			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thanks Kirium! 
<br />

<br />
While I don't know the scaling of damage mitigation with AC (or other stats), I have heard that the AC needs to be close to the ATK of the mob for significant mitigation.
<br />

<br />
At around 680, it is no wonder that Mages report mitigating damage better than their pets.
<br />

<br />
The mitigation needs to be adjusted to the mobs the mage is encountering on a day-to-day basis. This becomes increasingly important in grouping and raiding situations where Pet Affinity will become a primary source of pet heals. If the pet is taking twice the damage of the melee, it will, in effect only be getting half the group healing of those players. Spot heals will be twice as expensive in terms of time and mana on a per-event basis.
<br />

<br />
I only have access to data from a guild that is a two months into Time. The following data is meant to apply to players in that situation. If others have data from guilds at different points in the game, it will help to establish the state of affairs at other levels. I included all "active" members of our guild, with the exception of a couple recruits that joined us within the last month or so, from pre-elemental play.
<br />

<br />
The median is the "middle" value -- half above, half below. It is more appropriate than the conventional use of the mean to determine an "average" value as it does not heavily weight the outliers. It shows the "middle-of-the-road" player.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">Class Median Max&nbsp; &nbsp;Min
<br />
&nbsp;WAR&nbsp; &nbsp;1811&nbsp; 2056&nbsp; 1630
<br />

<br />
