<br />
&nbsp;Pet&nbsp; &nbsp; 680?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
(Only two Necros active with current Magelos)
<br />

<br />
If you consider that a mage pet is under the same stress from adds as the hybrids, you are looking for an AC of somethere in the 1500-1700 range. 
<br />

<br />
Warriors still have the best damage mitigation. Pets should be better than priests as priests can immediately self heal (unless the pet somehow knows how to self-heal when they get hit -- the delay in the UI and casting time of Mage pet heals is not a substitute for sub-four-second self heals.)
<br />

<br />
That suggests a boost of about 1000 AC for elemental/early-Time players, scaled appropriately for lower level/geared players, if AC is the primary driving force behind mitigation.
<br />

<br />
Additional Note:
<br />

<br />
Tuning for PoP mobs will not be sufficient. It is akin to tuning our current pets to Luclin mobs. Each expansion has resulted in XP mobs and group/raid encounters that are a step (or several steps) more stressing than the previous.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by itchyban on Mon Feb 02, 2004 6:06 pm; edited 6 times in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
