				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Very informative thread!
<br />

<br />
I don't believe the AC issue should be solved with another line of summoned gear, I am already summoning out the ying yang to equip my pet. 
<br />

<br />
I have a diffrent idea. When a pet is summoned he starts with a base AC, say the 650, then through the powers of programming the pet adds the AC of the master.  So theroetically if this worked today and I summoned an earth pet he would have 1525 AC (650 + 875 = 1525) This way the pet will scale with the mage over a long period of time.
<br />

<br />
Add in buffs and the normal summoned gear and the pet will be a viable defensive tool in many situations. The limitations would be based on gear and it would not get too overpowering because you don't find too many mages with 1000+ AC.
<br />

<br />
Just a thought<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234133" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ghetto_and_Proud</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.insidiousblood.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Insidious Blood</a>
