				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Something I've always wondered about...
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Drajeck wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">It has always been my understanding that pets had only 1 wrist and 1 ring slot, and that a second wrist/ring would be ignored.  Is this correct, or have I been holding back a couple slots that could be used?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
A very, very long time ago, there was some GM (not a Guide, nor was it a GM-admin) who said a pet had 8 slots for equipment. That's Primary/Secondary and 6 equipment slots?
<br />

<br />
I later came to presume that what he meant was that it's only possible for human/elf/troll NPC to equip those 8 slots in order to get a "visual effect". But how many slots an NPC really has to make use of is still a mystery to me.
<br />

<br />
Many changes has been done to the game since then and I'm quite sure that even if something was true then, it may not be the case today.
<br />

<br />
Why can't a developer just tell us? Or even better - give us the option to inspect our pets? It's not a "fun mystery", it's just annoying imho. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
