<br />

<br />
Well, pets seems to inherit the resists we have on at summoning time. I don't have a study to prove it, but when I hunt in Nurga I have noticed a difference against the Wizzie/Shaman mobs if I have Elemental Cloak, Circle of Seasons, etc. buffs up when I summon my pet. Without the buffs, petsky will eat the about 1/2 the nukes (my standard resists are mr/fr/cr ~80 unbuffed). With them I've never seen one stick for full.
<br />

<br />
Based on that, the precedence is set for buffed AC at summoning. Maybe its too complicated a coding task to compute unbuffed stats on the fly at summoning time. Certainly it would require an extra few bytes of data/character to store that. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyhow, this is a fascinating thread. I do find it ironic that I probably have an unbuffed AC that is a couple hundred points higher than my pet. I have 660 AC unbuffed at level 57, and my pets are level 45[Voc Air/water] or 48 [g.voc earth].
<br />

<br />
Question: Is there a useful test dummy available to the sub-60 crowd? I'd like to replicate these test with the Voc and G.Voc pets to see if how they do. If not, perhaps someone could run a test with them for me? 
<br />

<br />
I'm suspecting that pet stats and were missed on the G.Voc pets. Both G.Voc Earth and Air only got 50hp(!!!) upgrades over the Voc pets. For those who don't recall, 50hps at level 57 allows the pet to absorb one extra extra bash or kick from non-pop exp mobs in Velious, LoY and Luclin. Standard melee from those mobs is 100pts+. So its possible that they also received insignificant mitigation and AC increases.
<br />

<br />
Aqui<br />_________________<br />Aquilistor Apotropacus
<br />
58 Magician
<br />
Forsaken Conclave
<br />
Bertoxxulous
